      • portForwarding

        public FutureNAT portForwarding(FutureDiscover futureDiscover,
                                DiscoverBuilder builder)
        Setup UPNP or NATPMP port forwarding.
        Parameters:
        futureDiscover - The result of the discovery process. This information from the discovery process is important to setup UPNP or NATPMP. If this fails, then this future will also fail, and other means to connect to the network needs to be found.
        Returns:
        The future object that tells you if you are reachable (success), if UPNP or NATPMP could be setup and then you are reachable (success), or if it failed.

      • setupPortforwarding

        public Ports setupPortforwarding(String internalHost,
                                 Ports ports)
        The Dynamic and/or Private Ports are those from 49152 through 65535 (http://www.iana.org/assignments/port-numbers).
        Parameters:
        internalHost - The IP of the internal host
        Returns:
        The new external ports if port forwarding seemed to be successful, otherwise null
